– 2 –
1 (a) Under the supervision of a physician licensed pursuant to
2 chapter 630 or 633 of NRS, order, prescribe, possess and administer
3 controlled substances, poisons, dangerous drugs and devices to treat
4 a patient under the care of a licensed physician [in a critical access
5 hospital] in preparation for surgery or childbirth, during surgery or
6 childbirth and while a patient recovers from surgery or childbirth.
7 (b) Possess and administer controlled substances, poisons,
8 dangerous drugs and devices in other circumstances under which a
9 registered nurse is authorized to possess and administer controlled
10 substances, poisons, dangerous drugs and devices.
11 2. A certified registered nurse anesthetist shall not order or
12 prescribe a controlled substance, poison, dangerous drug or device
13 except as authorized by paragraph (a) of subsection 1.
14 [3. As used in this section, “critical access hospital” means a
15 hospital which has been certified as a critical access hospital by the
16 Secretary of Health and Human Services pursuant to 42 U.S.C.
17 1395i-4(e).]
18 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
